wn in PG 5.3.5.\n34\nPUBLIC\nQuarterly Stability Assessment (QSA)\n35\nPUBLIC STAGE 2: Resource Registration and Modeling \nMilestones\n36\nRegistration \nof RE\nIdentify \nMRD\nSubmit Full \nRegistration Data\nEPS Meter / \nTelemetry \nSet Up\nPUBLIC\nStage 2: Registration and Modeling\n37 The Resource Integration and Ongoing Operations – Interconnection Services (RIOO-IS) is  ...    needed for ERCOT systems. The contents of RIOO-IS are governed by the Resource Registration Glossary. Each field in RIOO-IS must be submitted at certain times during Stage 1, 2 and 3 as indicated by the following columns in the Glossary:\n• Full Interconnection Study (FIS)  ...    within 15 days of the deadline may not get processed in time to be included in the \ndesired PLD! Once the data has reached the Production Load Date (PLD) where the generator(s) are modeled in the Network Operations Model and preparing for energization, the RE shall use RIOO-Resource Services (RIOO-RS) to submit any changes to that data.\nPUBLIC\nStage 3: Resource Commissioning Milestones 38\nSubmit \nCommissioning \nPlan\nPart 1: \nEnergization\nPart 2: \nSynchronization\nPart 3: Full \nCommissioning\nPUBLIC STAGE 3: Energization, Synchronization and \nCommissioning \n39\nERCOT New Generator Commissioning Checklist The three-part ERC"
